}} 'Paris Saint-Germain Football Club', also known simply as 'Paris Saint-
Germain' (familiarly as 'Paris SG' or 'PSG'), is a professional association
football club based in Paris, France. The capital club was founded on 12 August
1970, thanks to the merger of Paris FC and . PSG has been playing in Ligue 1
since 1974. {{cite news
| title = History url = http://www.psg.fr/en/Club/601001/History work = PSG.fr
| date = 30 May 2013 accessdate = 26 June 2013}} Paris Saint-Germain have
| won 3 Ligue 1, 1 Ligue 2, 8 Coupe de France, 3 Coupe de la Ligue, 2 TrophÃ©e
| des Champions, 1 UEFA Cup Winners' Cup and 1 UEFA Intertoto Cup. {{cite news title = Palmares url =
| http://www.psg.fr/fr/Club/608001/Palmares work = PSG.fr date = 12 May 2013
| accessdate = 13 May 2013}}

The Parc des Princes has been the home stadium of Paris Saint-Germain since
1974. {{cite news
| title = stade Parc des Princes url = http://niko17.footblog.fr/377427/stade-Parc-des-
| Princes/ work = Footblog date = 9 December 2006 accessdate =29 January
| 2012}} The Camp des Loges has been operating as a training centre for
| the club since 1970. {{cite news title = Le Camp des Loges url
| = http://www.infopsg.com/le-club/le-camp-des-loges/ work = Info PSG accessdate
| =29 January 2012}} The Tournoi de Paris has been hosted by PSG at the
| Parc des Princes since 1975. {{cite news title = Le PSG
| relance le Tournoi de Paris dÃ¨s 2010 url = http://www.psgmag.net/1876-Le-PSG-relance-le-Tournoi-de-
| Paris.html work = PSG MAG date = 24 December 2009 accessdate =5 February
| 2012}} The crest and shirt of Paris Saint-Germain were mainly designed
| by Daniel Hechter. {{cite news title = Robert Vicot : " Je
| suis l'initiateur de l'Ã©chauffement collectif " url =
| http://psg70.free.fr/interviewvicot.htm work = PSG70 accessdate =9 May
| 2013}} The crest represents Paris through the Eiffel Tower and Saint-Germain-en-
| Laye through the fleur-de-lys between the legs of the tower. {{cite news title = Blasons, Logos, Ãcussons du PSG url =
| http://psg70.free.fr/blasons.htm work = PSG70 accessdate =7 October
| 2010}} The shirt is blue with a red central vertical bar framed by white
| edgings. {{cite news title = Historique des maillots
| du PSG : les annÃ©es 1970 url = http://www.psgmag.net/548-Historique-des-maillots-du-PSG-
| les.html work = PSG MAG date = 16 June 2010 accessdate = 8 July 2013}}
| Allez Paris Saint-Germain, to the tune of "Go West" by Pet Shop Boys, is the
| official anthem of PSG. The lyrics of "Go West" were rewritten following
| suggestions made by the fans. Germain the lynx, meanwhile, is the mascot of
| the club. {{Cite news title = Le PSG prend un nouveau virage url = http://www.psg.fr/fr/Article/003001/Article/49547/Le-PSG-prend-un-nouveau-
| virage work = PSG.fr date = 23 July 2010 accessdate =26 July 2010}}

Paris Saint-Germain shares an intense rivalry with Olympique de Marseille and
contest the most notorious football match in France, known as Le Classique. {{cite news
| title = France's passion play url =
| http://www.fifa.com/classicfootball/clubs/rivalries/newsid=1037223/ work =
| FIFA accessdate =25 February 2013}} PSG is the second best-supported
| football club in France after arch-rivals Marseille. {{cite
| news title = Capital gains: well-connected PSG's revival is good for French
| football url = http://fourfourtwo.com/blogs/thefrenchconnection/archive/2011/12/21/capital-
| gains-well-connected-psg-s-revival-is-good-for-french-football.aspx work =
| FourFourTwo date = 21 December 2011 accessdate =13 February 2012}} "Ici
| c'est Paris" (This is Paris) is one of the club's most popular mottos. {{Cite news title = Paris is Earning url = http://theclassical.org/articles/paris-is-
| earning work = The Classical date = 11 January 2012 accessdate =13 February
| 2012}} Qatar Investment Authority has been the sole shareholder of Paris
| Saint-Germain since 2012. {{cite news title = Le Qatar sans
| limite url = http://www.leparisien.fr/psg-foot-paris-saint-germain/le-qatar-sans-limite-
| 07-03-2012-1893594.php work = Le Parisien date = 7 March 2012 accessdate =7
| March 2012}} Following QIA's takeover, PSG became the richest club in
| France and one of the richest clubs in the world. {{cite
| news title = Paris: The New Madrid url = http://www.thepursuitofvictory.com/2011/12/paris-new-
| madrid.html work = The Pursuit of Victory date = 28 December 2011 accessdate
| =2 February 2012}}
